==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rancorous
<hw>Ran"cor*ous</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧"k⟦etil⟧r*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>rancuros</ets>.]</ety> <def>Full of rancor;
evincing, or caused by, rancor; deeply malignant; implacably spiteful or
malicious; intensely virulent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So flamed his eyes with rage and <qex>rancorous</qex> ire.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rancorously</ent>⟦br⟧
